              body: "'Riches in the niches' is repeated so often it sounds hollow, so here is the actual mechanism. Specificity raises three numbers at once.\n\n**Conversion**: 'marketing coach' competes with everyone; 'marketing coach for wedding photographers' makes a wedding photographer feel found. Copy that names the reader's exact situation converts multiples better than generic copy.\n\n**Price**: buyers pay a specialist premium because perceived likelihood — remember the value equation — spikes when the provider has solved *their exact* problem before. A niche case study is worth ten generic ones.\n\n**Referrals**: specialists are describable in one sentence, so word of mouth transmits without loss. Nobody refers 'a guy who does various marketing things.'\n\nThe fear is always 'I will run out of people.' Almost no solo creator ever saturates a niche — even narrow niches contain more buyers than you can serve. Go narrower than feels comfortable, dominate, then widen from a position of strength."
