              body: "Microcopy is the text nearest the moment of commitment — button labels, form hints, the line under the price, the PS at the end of an email. It is tiny real estate with outsized leverage, because it speaks at maximum anxiety.\n\nWorking principles:\n\n- **Buttons state value, not mechanics**: 'Get the free checklist' beats 'Submit.' First person often lifts response — 'Start my trial' over 'Start your trial.'\n- **Kill anxiety at the point it spikes**: 'No spam, unsubscribe anytime' beside the email field; 'Card not charged until day 8' beside the trial button; 'Takes 2 minutes' beside the form.\n- **The PS is prime property**: in email, skimmers read the subject, the first line, and the PS. Put a proof point or the deadline there.\n- **Match the click's promise**: the words on the button must reappear on the page it leads to, or trust leaks at the seam.\n\nAudit any funnel by reading only its microcopy. You will usually find the leak within minutes."
